{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BGFz85dpjwodCHcGLeq9Dw","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# themedrops.com - Theme sharing site\n     2→\n     3→This project is to build a website that is a gallery of \"themes\".\n     4→These themes are color/typography/etc. themes that can be requested through an API to give back the theme as JSON - you can optionally ask for the theme in different ways using query parameters, like HSL instead of RGB etc.\n     5→Themes should include fonts as well as colors, and anything else that makes sense, but everytihng is optional.\n     6→Seed the site with a system user, and themes under this user.\n     7→\n     8→All previews (like cards in the gallery) should themselves be previews of the theme itself.\n     9→\n    10→The schema of the theme should be designed to be used in all applications, for example in VS Code, in Discord, in Jetbrains, in custom websites, etc.\n    11→In fact, in this website itself it should allow you to use and apply any theme, e.g. this site should have a theme switcher that allows you to select any theme from this website.\n    12→\n    13→Users can signup and create their own themes.\n    14→Themes should be fork-able, so people can make minor adjustments to themes and rename them to make them their own.\n    15→Users should have a profile page similar to like a youtube profile.\n    16→Themes can be commented on, starred, shared, etc.\n    17→\n    18→The home page should be some sort of feed that includes a mix of popular/new themes, and also people commenting on the themes.\n    19→\n    20→If you've run out of ideas, create some new ones.\n    21→\n    22→This is a design-oriented project, it should look excellent from a design perspective.\n    23→\n    24→There should be a VSCode extension built in a sub-folder that allows you to install the extension to vscode, and then to use any theme available on themedrops.com\n    25→Think of other extension to build as well.\n    26→Maybe also a way to easily use themes inside Tailwind.\n    27→\n    28→The theme details page should make it clear how to call the API for this theme also.\n    29→\n    30→# Tech Stack\n    31→\n    32→NextJS on Vercel, Tailwind, Typescript, Convex.dev, Convex Username/Password Auth\n    33→\n    34→# Testing\n    35→\n    36→Make sure to test your work in a browser upon each iteration.\n    37→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"531f43a4-ebc3-4fb3-8c9b-48ab32ad838e","uuid":"47d2cd33-2b4a-420d-a23a-4959101409a7","timestamp":"2026-03-28T00:14:27.336Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/matt/code/themedrops/PLAN.md","content":"# themedrops.com - Theme sharing site\n\nThis project is to build a website that is a gallery of \"themes\".\nThese themes are color/typography/etc. themes that can be requested through an API to give back the theme as JSON - you can optionally ask for the theme in different ways using query parameters, like HSL instead of RGB etc.\nThemes should include fonts as well as colors, and anything else that makes sense, but everytihng is optional.\nSeed the site with a system user, and themes under this user.\n\nAll previews (like cards in the gallery) should themselves be previews of the theme itself.\n\nThe schema of the theme should be designed to be used in all applications, for example in VS Code, in Discord, in Jetbrains, in custom websites, etc.\nIn fact, in this website itself it should allow you to use and apply any theme, e.g. this site should have a theme switcher that allows you to select any theme from this website.\n\nUsers can signup and create their own themes.\nThemes should be fork-able, so people can make minor adjustments to themes and rename them to make them their own.\nUsers should have a profile page similar to like a youtube profile.\nThemes can be commented on, starred, shared, etc.\n\nThe home page should be some sort of feed that includes a mix of popular/new themes, and also people commenting on the themes.\n\nIf you've run out of ideas, create some new ones.\n\nThis is a design-oriented project, it should look excellent from a design perspective.\n\nThere should be a VSCode extension built in a sub-folder that allows you to install the extension to vscode, and then to use any theme available on themedrops.com\nThink of other extension to build as well.\nMaybe also a way to easily use themes inside Tailwind.\n\nThe theme details page should make it clear how to call the API for this theme also.\n\n# Tech Stack\n\nNextJS on Vercel, Tailwind, Typescript, Convex.dev, Convex Username/Password Auth\n\n# Testing\n\nMake sure to test your work in a browser upon each iteration.\n","numLines":37,"startLine":1,"totalLines":37}}}
